                        <summary>
                            
                            <p>This inscription records the death of a hero named <hi rend="bold">Todupatti Mātiragaṉ</hi> (probably a mahout),<note>See <hi rend="italic">S.I.I.</hi> Vol. VIII, No. 739.</note> on the day when the village (i.e. Olakkūr) was destroyed in the confusion caused by <hi rend="bold">Kampapperumāḷ</hi> with his elephants. A figure of this hero advancing with a drawn sword in his right hand is also represented on the stone.</p>						
                            
                        </summary>
                    </msContents>
