            <div type="commentary">
                <p>In the same village is found an inscription (No. 356 of 1909) attributable to the 6th century A.D., engraved below a seated image of a goddess flanked by a lamp and canopied by an umbrella. It reads: 1. <foreign>piritivi viṭapā-</foreign> 2. <foreign>ṅkurati arai-</foreign> 3. <foreign>can ceyvitta[tu] <supplied reason="undefined"><g type="ddanda">.</g></supplied></foreign></p>
            </div>
            
